history.content: It should be fine to phase 2, but part of the enrollment dropoff for the current semester is explained by Professor Sahai's arduous assignments, particularly before the drop deadline. It's unclear how next semester's professors (Moritz Hardt and Ben Recht; latter has taught the course before) will handle Professor Sahai's restructuring of the course. If they revert to previous iterations of the course with lighter or less frequent homeworks, fewer people may be cleared off the waitlist, particularly with the ever-rising popularity of the course.

Hi all, 

I'm currently declared LSCS and was wondering if I should still Phase I CS189 to get the course for this fall. Based on previous enrollment (from FA2017) it looks like it should be okay, but does anyone have any other thoughts?
history.subject: Phase I CS189?
